properties needed for version 5.0.0. There's a comment about Netty 4.2.x requiring explicit unsafe access on Java 25 for native runs. Since 5.0.1 also depends on vertx-core 5.0.1 and Netty 4.2.2, I need to confirm if a specific system property, like `sun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow`, is necessary.\\n\\nI'm questioning if that would enable \\\"meaningful coverage.\\\" Without proper Native Image verification, it seems the native run fails, impacting coverage. I might need to research the dependencies tree and consider using a temporary Gradle dependency to avoid modifying the repository.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5qksTWF5Y93ysqbMKgs5pUdm|fc_08c3680ff9754fbc016a3ffba042e08194b64b969f298ea36b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; cat > pom.xml <<'EOF'\n<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\"><modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion><groupId>x</groupId><artifactId>x</artifactId><version>1</version><dependencies><dependency><groupId>io.vertx</groupId><artifactId>vertx-web-client</artifactId><version>5.0.1</version></dependency></dependencies></project>\nEOF\nmvn -q dependency:tree -Dscope=runtime -DoutputType=text", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1313, "output": 629, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21910, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782578071255, "responseId": "resp_08c3680ff9754fbc016a3ffb97b0c48194aea1cfa4b3f0081a"}}
